# nRF52840 — Reed Sensor

Zephyr BLE door/window reed sensor. Advertises open/closed state and battery SOC. Supports multiple instances via `CONFIG_BT_DEVICE_NAME` — each physical sensor gets its own build directory and device name.

## Hardware

- **MCU:** nRF52840 (Pro Micro form factor)
- **Board:** `promicro_nrf52840`
- **Interface:** Reed switch input, BLE advertising

## Source Files

| File | Description |
|:-----|:------------|
| `src/main.c` | BLE advertising, reed state, battery reporting |
| `src/battery.c` | Battery SOC measurement |
| `src/flash_log.c` | Flash-backed event logging |
| `src/fatal_hook.c` | Fatal error handler |

## Environment Setup

```bash
source ~/zephyrproject/.venv/bin/activate
export ZEPHYR_BASE=~/zephyrproject/zephyr
```

## Build

**Entry sensor (ReedSensor1):**
```bash
west build -p always -b promicro_nrf52840 \
  -d ~/embedded-iot-hub/nrf52840/reed-sensor/build-entry \
  ~/embedded-iot-hub/nrf52840/reed-sensor \
  -- -DCONFIG_BT_DEVICE_NAME=\"ReedSensor1\" -DCONFIG_DEBUG=y
```

**Window sensor (ReedSensor2):**
```bash
west build -p always -b promicro_nrf52840 \
  -d ~/embedded-iot-hub/nrf52840/reed-sensor/build-window \
  ~/embedded-iot-hub/nrf52840/reed-sensor \
  -- -DCONFIG_BT_DEVICE_NAME=\"ReedSensor2\" -DCONFIG_DEBUG=y
```

Additional sensors follow the same pattern with unique `build-<name>` directories and `ReedSensor3..6`.

## Flash

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /mnt/nrf52
sudo mount /dev/sda /mnt/nrf52

# Entry
sudo cp build-entry/zephyr/zephyr.uf2 /mnt/nrf52/

# Window
sudo cp build-window/zephyr/zephyr.uf2 /mnt/nrf52/

sync && sudo umount /mnt/nrf52
```

## Monitor

```bash
minicom -D /dev/ttyACM0 -b 115200
```

## Teardown

```bash
deactivate
```
